{"name": "robotframework-ghareports", "metadata": {"name": "robotframework-ghareports", "version": "0.5.1", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Environment :: Console", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Intended Audience :: End Users/Desktop", "Intended Audience :: Information Technology", "Intended Audience :: System Administrators", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries", "Topic :: Software Development :: Quality Assurance", "Topic :: Software Development :: Testing", "Topic :: Utilities"], "home_page": null, "license": "GPLV3", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["robotframework", "wrapt"], "summary": "Simple github action summary report for robotframework", "upload_time": 1734960202}, "documentation": ["robotframework-ghareports\n=========================\n\n\nThis project enables robot framework to generate Github Job Summary for a testrun. You can either use it as listener or standalone command\nline tool. When executed, it checks if environment variable GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY exists and if it does, it exposes test results\nto a PR - example output looks something like [this](https://github.com/rasjani/robotframework-ghareports/blob/main/example_step_summary.md)\n\nMain purpose for standalone tool is that with it, you can use pabot or rerun failed test cases once you have combined the logs to a single\noutput.xml, you can use  `ghareports` to generate the summary.\n\n## Installation\n\n```shell\npython -mpip install robotframework-ghareports\n```\n\n## Usage as listener\n\n```shell\nrobot --listener GHAReports .\n```\n\n## Usage as standalone tool\n\n```\nghareports -r path/to/robot/output.xml\n```\n\nHelp that shows all available arguments\n\n```\nghareports --help\n```\n\n## Additional\n\nIf you want to limit the width of the tables in the summary, you can provide an argument to the listener like this:\n\n```shell\nrobot --listener GHAReports:35 .\n```\n\nor\n```shell\nghareports -r output.xml --width=35\n```\n\nThis will split each cell with string content at every 35 characters into a new line.\n\nAnd if you want to generate the summary even  if a) you are not running in Github *or* you want to generate extra summary file independent of\nGithub actions, pass report_file argument to the listener like this:\n\n```shell\nrobot --listener GHAReports:report_file=extra_summary.md\n```\nor\n\n```shell\nrobot --listener GHAReports:34:extra_summary.md\n```\n\nor via standalone tool:\n\n\n```shell\nghareports -r output.xml -m example_step_summary.md\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "GHAReports", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "GHAReports.GHAReports", "xref": {"fqname": "GHAReports.GHAReports.GHAReports", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "GHAReports.cli", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "GHAReports.cli.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "GHAReports.cli.GHAReportsVisitor", "bases": ["ResultVisitor"], "methods": [{"name": "GHAReports.cli.GHAReportsVisitor.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cell_width_in_characters", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "markdown_file", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "GHAReports.cli.GHAReportsVisitor.start_suite", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "suite", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "GHAReports.cli.GHAReportsVisitor.end_suite", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "suite", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "GHAReports.cli.GHAReportsVisitor.start_test", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "test", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "GHAReports.cli.GHAReportsVisitor.end_test", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "test", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "GHAReports.cli.GHAReportsVisitor.end_result", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "result", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "GHAReports.cli.GHAReportsVisitor.visit_message", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "message", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "GHAReports.mdgen", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [{"name": "GHAReports.mdgen.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "GHAReports.mdgen.MD_FENCE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "GHAReports.mdgen.MD_HEADER", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "GHAReports.mdgen.MD_HORIZONTAL_RULE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "GHAReports.mdgen.MD_CODE_BLOCK", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "GHAReports.mdgen.MD_SINGLE_LINE_BLOCKQUOTE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "GHAReports.mdgen.MD_MULTILINE_BLOCKQUOTE", "type": null, "documentation": ["GitLab only"]}, {"name": "GHAReports.mdgen.MD_INLINE_CODE_HL", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "GHAReports.mdgen.MD_LIST_ELEMENT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "GHAReports.mdgen.MD_TABLE_ALIGN_LEFT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "GHAReports.mdgen.MD_TABL